sleep()
not what we want. we awant to do NSTimer to fire _ seconds later with the thing we want done.
usleep is microseconds
sleep(2 seconds) = usleep(2000000)

sleep(forTimeInterval:)

    No run loop processing occurs while the thread is blocked.

    class func sleep(forTimeInterval ti: TimeInterval)
    Parameters
    ti
        The duration of the sleep.


    Stopping a Thread

    class func sleep(until: Date)
        Blocks the current thread until the time specified.
    class func exit()
        Terminates the current thread.
    func cancel()
        Changes the cancelled state of the receiver to indicate that it should exit.

